Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine light brown. Circular stamp.
Curator's comments: Name Eukratidas. Trimmed. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, CEALEX CRI(cket ground) 462.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0376)
